-- Hungary Stocks: OTP Bank, Mol Shares Move in Budapest Trading
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-06-20T09:42:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-20/hungary-stocks-otp-bank-mol-shares-move-in-budapest-trading.html
The benchmark  BUX (BUX)  index fell 0.3
percent to 17,745.62 by 11:23 a.m. in Budapest.  The following are among the most active shares in the
Hungarian market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP)  , Hungary’s largest lender, fell 0.4
percent to 3,761 forint as investors awaited the outcome of the
 Federal Reserve ’s monetary-policy meeting for clues on how much
central banks will bolster the world economy.  Mol Nyrt. (MOL)  , Hungary’s largest refiner, fell 0.5
percent to 16,625 forint. Brent oil dropped for a third day in
London on speculation that U.S. supplies may have shrunk less
than estimated.  To contact the reporter on this story:
